  "prompt": "What is the toughest question ever asked in a interview?",
  "response": "Interview questions can vary widely based on the industry, position, and specific company culture. However, one question often regarded as particularly difficult and thought-provoking is:\n\n**\"What is your biggest weakness?\"**\n\nThis question is tough because it requires candidates to be self-aware, honest, and insightful while also framing their answers in a way that doesn't undermine their candidacy. It tests both the candidate's ability to reflect on their personal development areas and their skills in presenting challenges as opportunities for growth.\n\nOther challenging interview questions include:\n\n1. **\"Tell me about a time you failed.\"** - This requires vulnerability and the ability to discuss personal setbacks positively.\n   \n2. **\"Where do you see yourself in five years?\"** - This questions long-term aspirations and compatibility with the company's trajectory.\n\n3. **\"Why should we hire you?\"** - It's a prompt for the candidate to differentiate themselves from others and make a compelling case.\n\nUltimately, what makes a question tough often depends on how candidates interpret and respond to it, as well as the pressure of the interview context.",
